  "texts": [
    "The parameter C is considered a regularisation parameter in the sense that the higher its value, the less tolerance there will be for margin violations, hence the wider the tube will be, decreasing the number of support vectors and therefore decreasing the regularisation strength (increasing the variance).",
    "In this study, we (1) h t = argmin h∈H EL(y, F t-1 (x) + h t (x)).",
    "(2) implemented an extensive grid search that yielded the following best hyperparameters: C = 1, ǫ = 0.01 and a 3rd-degree polynomial kernel.",
    "The ǫ-insensitive loss function used to train our SVR model is given by Equation 3:",
    "where ε ≥ 0 defines the maximum error, N is the number of data points, y(i) is the i-th measurement, and ŷ(i) is its corresponding prediction, made with network weights θ. LSTM Recurrent Neural Networks (RNN) are a class of neural networks that is powerful for modelling sequence data such as time series or natural language 42."
